Documents that don't have "word/styles.xml" will throw an exception.

In docx/\_\_init\_\_.py:40, the code runs ```_open_entry``` without first checking for the property.

I corrected it in a local build by wrapping it with ```_has_entry```, and returning an empty Styles object.

I modified the constructor of Styles to get an empty styles constructor.

```Python
    def __init__(self, paragraph_styles=None, character_styles=None):
        if paragraph_styles and character_styles:
            self._paragraph_styles = paragraph_styles
            self._character_styles = character_styles
        else:
            self._paragraph_styles = {}
            self._character_styles = {}
```

I wanted to know if this is a good way to handle the issue.

Here is what I would like to do:

@api.doc(documentation for GET method, documentation for PUT method)
class A():
    def get():
        pass
    def put():
        pass

I couldn't find any solution on flask-restplus documentation other than defining doc explicitly before each method.
Any explanation on how to achieve this task or whether this is impossible to achieve or any pointer to this context would really help. Thank you @noirbizarre Hope to hear something back from you.

